						<p>Increase in diagnostic coverage</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<h2>Key Learnings</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Context is King</strong>: RAG architecture proved essential for grounding LLM responses in actual database metrics rather than hallucinated insights</li>
					<li><strong>Agent Specialization</strong>: Breaking down diagnostics into specialized agents (CPU, Memory, I/O) improved accuracy and reduced token costs</li>
					<li><strong>Prompt Engineering Matters</strong>: Iterative refinement of prompts increased diagnostic accuracy from 72% to 94%</li>
					<li><strong>Human-in-the-Loop</strong>: Critical alerts still require human verification - AI augments but doesn't replace expertise</li>
				</ul>

